




TY  - JOUR
T1  - Decomposing Learning by Doing in New Plants
AU  - Bahk, Byong-Hyong
AU  - Gort, Michael
Y1  - 1993/08/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/261888
DO  - 10.1086/261888
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 561
EP  - 583
VL  - 101
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - The paper examines learning by doing in the context of a production function in which the other arguments are labor, human capital, physical capital, and vintage as a proxy for embodied technical change in physical capital. Learning is further decomposed into organization learning, capital learning, and manual task learning. The model is tested with time-series and cross-section data for various samples of up to 2,150 plants over a 14-year period.
AB  - The paper examines learning by doing in the context of a production function in which the other arguments are labor, human capital, physical capital, and vintage as a proxy for embodied technical change in physical capital. Learning is further decomposed into organization learning, capital learning, and manual task learning. The model is tested with time-series and cross-section data for various samples of up to 2,150 plants over a 14-year period.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/261888
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/261888
Y2  - 2024/03/23
